---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { Nav } from "../components/Nav";

const REPO = "https://github.com/0x-copilot-dev/0x-copilot";
---

<Base
  title="Tokenomics — 0xCopilot"
  description="50% fair launch, 25% team & contributors, 25% automated capital formation. Every allocation has a job."
  here="token"
>
  <Nav here="token" />

  <header class="hero">
    <span class="tag">● Not launched · no contract address exists yet</span>

    <h1>Every allocation has <em>a job.</em></h1>

    <p class="hero__sub">
      0xCopilot launches on Virtuals Protocol. Three buckets, no hidden fourth.
      Half the supply belongs to the market from the first block, a quarter is
      reserved for the people who build the thing, and a quarter is a funding
      engine the protocol runs — not a wallet anyone can reach into.
    </p>

    <div
      class="alloc"
      role="img"
      aria-label="Supply allocation: 50 percent fair launch, 25 percent team and contributors, 25 percent automated capital formation"
    >
      <div class="alloc__seg" data-k="market">50% &nbsp;FAIR LAUNCH</div>
      <div class="alloc__seg" data-k="people">25% &nbsp;ESOP</div>
      <div class="alloc__seg" data-k="engine">25% &nbsp;ACF</div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="band" style="border-top:none;padding-top:0">
    <div class="bucket" data-k="market">
      <div class="bucket__pct">50%<span>The market</span></div>
      <div class="bucket__body">
        <h3>Fair launch — tradable from the first block.</h3>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            Half the supply, in the pool, at launch. No lock, no vesting, no
            allowlist, no preferential price. Everyone holding this half bought
            it on the open curve at the same public price as everyone else.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>There is no founder pre-buy.</strong> No insider bucket sits
            in front of the market on the curve. The largest single allocation in
            this project belongs to the people who buy it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="facts">
          <li><b>Lock</b><span>None — live at launch.</span></li>
          <li>
            <b>Float</b><span
              >Grows one buy at a time. The pool is inventory, not a holder.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Supply</b><span
              ><span class="tbd">FILL: fixed supply</span> — set at launch under the
              Virtuals framework and published here before the first block.</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bucket" data-k="people">
      <div class="bucket__pct">25%<span>The people</span></div>
      <div class="bucket__body">
        <h3>Team &amp; contributors — the ESOP pool.</h3>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            Reserved for the people who ship the product. Not a founder
            allocation — a pool that pays out as grants to the engineers,
            designers and contributors who actually build 0xCopilot, each grant
            carrying its own vesting on top of the protocol lock.
          </p>
          <p>
            Unallocated tokens sit still in a published wallet. A transfer out of
            this pool means a person joined — nothing else.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="facts">
          <li>
            <b>Protocol lock</b><span
              ><span class="tbd">FILL: lock period</span> from launch, enforced on-chain
              by Virtuals.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Protocol vest</b><span
              ><span class="tbd">FILL: vest window + shape</span> into a pool wallet
              the company controls.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Grants</b><span
              >Made from the pool with their own multi-year schedule and cliff,
              sized by role. A grant re-locks; it does not unlock.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Early vest</b><span
              ><span class="tbd">FILL: FDV early-vest trigger, if any</span> — Virtuals
              can start the vest early above a valuation threshold. If that applies
              here it gets stated on this line, not discovered later.</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bucket" data-k="engine">
      <div class="bucket__pct">25%<span>The engine</span></div>
      <div class="bucket__body">
        <h3>Automated Capital Formation — funding tied to proof.</h3>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            The funding engine, executed by the protocol rather than by anyone's
            judgment. As valuation rises, ACF converts tokens to USDC in small
            automated steps and routes the proceeds to the operating company —
            hiring, infrastructure, audits, the work.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>No growth, no funding.</strong> Capital only forms when the
            market has verified the work. There is no discretionary insider
            selling from this bucket, because no insider can execute it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <ul class="facts">
          <li>
            <b>Trigger</b><span
              ><span class="tbd">FILL: starting FDV</span> — below that, ACF releases
              nothing.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li>
            <b>Mechanism</b><span
              >Automated conversion at each additional
              <span class="tbd">FILL: FDV step</span>, continuing to
              <span class="tbd">FILL: FDV ceiling</span>.</span
            >
          </li>
          <li><b>Proceeds</b><span>USDC growth capital to the operating company.</span></li>
          <li>
            <b>Execution</b><span
              >Protocol-run and on-chain. Not a wallet with a human signer.</span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="band">
    <div class="eyebrow">Day one</div>
    <h2>Insider-linked supply that can move at launch: zero.</h2>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Only fair-launch tokens can trade on day one. The ESOP is behind a
        protocol lock, ACF hasn't triggered, and there is no pre-buy to unlock.
        Every insider-linked token is locked, vested, or protocol-executed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="note">
      <strong>Where the operating money comes from.</strong> Day-to-day costs are
      meant to run on the protocol's trade-fee stream, not on selling supply — and
      scale capital comes from ACF, which only fires when valuation rises.
      <span class="tbd">FILL: fee split + operations share</span> once the launch
      parameters are fixed, so this line matches what's actually on-chain.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="band">
    <div class="eyebrow">Commitments</div>
    <h2>The rules we hold ourselves to.</h2>
    <ul class="facts">
      <li>
        <b>01</b><span
          >Every wallet is published and labeled — the ESOP pool and the company
          treasury, watchable on-chain from day one. There are no allocations
          other than the three on this page.</span
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <b>02</b><span
          >The ESOP wallet moves only by grant. Unallocated tokens sit visibly
          still.</span
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <b>03</b><span
          >No founder pre-buy, at launch or after, from any bucket on this page.</span
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        <b>04</b><span
          >The protocol holds the keys where it counts. Locks, vesting and ACF
          execution are enforced on-chain by Virtuals — the parts you'd otherwise
          have to trust are the parts we can't touch.</span
        >
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="legal">
      <p>
        The 0xCopilot token is not equity, and carries no dividend, revenue
        entitlement, or claim on company assets. Nothing on this page is an offer
        of securities or investment advice.
      </p>
      <p>
        Protocol mechanics — locks, vesting and ACF thresholds — follow the
        Virtuals Protocol framework and are enforced on-chain. The ESOP grant
        policy is a 0xCopilot commitment, published here and verifiable by
        watching the labeled wallets.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong style="color:var(--signal)">No contract address exists yet.</strong>
        When one does it will be published here and on
        <a href="https://x.com/Copilot0x" rel="noopener">@Copilot0x</a>. Any
        address you see anywhere else, before then, is not ours.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="foot">
    <div class="foot__links">
      <a href="./">Home</a>
      <a href={REPO} rel="noopener">GitHub ↗</a>
      <a href="https://x.com/Copilot0x" rel="noopener">@Copilot0x ↗</a>
    </div>
    <p class="foot__fine">
      © 2026 0xCopilot · Ask · Steer · Ship<br />
      Nothing on this site is financial advice or an offer of securities.
    </p>
  </footer>
</Base>
